bri; font-size:11pt"> succumb to apoplexy should he be alive today.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The BBC has rested on the laurels won during WW2 and such </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">innovative programmes carried on the less pop-resistant topics of Science, Philosophy innovative Drama and Satiric expose. Programmes such as TW3, Spitting Image, The Ascent of Man, Tomorrows World even live entertainment such as </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Old Grey </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Whistle Test</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> or M</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">orecambe and Wise</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to name but two,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> laid</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> bench marks which I fear have sadly been over written by the convenience of extensive pre-recording and editing which may well serve to satisfy ‘professional’ standard of approval but serve to disconnect with</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> reality</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The News service and perhaps the most important service element of the BBC brief certainly carries the PC Multicultural agenda in to every living-room despite the fact that the nation has never been exposed to any meaningful debate at any stage, whe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ther </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">this is deemed desir</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">able or not by the wider population as a whole. This pro-European agenda coupled with the diminished role of our own Parliament’s autonomy seems more akin to Orwell’s 1984</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and the BBC seemingly simply trots out the required supine messa</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ge without regard to balance of public opinion.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The cult of celebrity news-readers is also a cause for concern as it now follows the familiar routine of ritual exchanges of personal pleasantries for simply doing what they are supposed to be doing with deta</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ched professionalism. Even the weather reporters are in on the act virtually bypassing the fact that they are addressing the entire nation and not just their pals behind the news desk.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This matter however irritating is surpassed by the arrogance of the BBC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to remunerate its self-serving participants at rates grossly in excess of the average wage of the licence payers on whom they depend for their existence. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The BBC needs to revisit its original and contextual remit from the 1930s as though it was being reb</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">orn and only then will it realise how far it has come from its conceptual and ethical roots – but I won’t be holding my breath in expectation.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>